<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-12-09T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-12-09T21:00:00-05:00" n="432" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 851.857/40</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)<note n="2" xml:id="d432fn2">The same to the Ambassador in Austria-Hungary,
                                    No. 1447.</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-12-09T21:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">December 9, 1916, 9 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>3656. Department advised that unarmed French ship <persName>
                                    <hi rend="italic">John Lambert</hi></persName>, Montreal to
                                Havre with cargo of coal, was cannonaded without notice by submarine
                                of unknown nationality and sunk between Havre and Falmouth November
                                22 last. Five or six Americans were among the crew.</p>
                            <p>Please bring this case to notice of Foreign Minister with request for
                                prompt investigation and report.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>